## Link to this sectionUsage#

To train a YOLO26n model on the COCO8 dataset for 100 [epochs](https://www.ultralytics.com/glossary/epoch) with an image size of 640, use the following examples. For a full list of training options, see the [YOLO Training documentation](/modes/train).

Train Example
    
    
    from ultralytics import YOLO
    
    # Load a pretrained YOLO26n model
    model = YOLO("yolo26n.pt")
    
    # Train the model on COCO8
    results = model.train(data="coco8.yaml", epochs=100, imgsz=640)

